            <p>A: Groq offers the most generous free tier with 1,000 requests/day, 14.4K tokens/minute, and no credit card required. Google Gemini 2.0 Flash is the best unlimited free option.</p>

            <p><strong>Q: Do I need a credit card to try AI APIs?</strong></p>
            <p>A: Many providers do not require one. Groq, Google Gemini, Zhipu, DeepSeek, FreeModel, OpenRouter, and Baidu all offer free access without a credit card.</p>

            <p><strong>Q: Which free tier is best for Chinese developers?</strong></p>
            <p>A: <a href="https://freemodel.dev/invite/FRE-7a3b6220" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">FreeModel</a> offers free credits with direct access from China (no proxy needed). Zhipu GLM-3-Turbo is completely free for Chinese-language tasks. ByteDance and Alibaba Cloud also offer generous free quotas.</p>

            <p><strong>Q: How much can I build with free API tiers alone?</strong></p>
            <p>A: A surprising amount. Groq free tier (1,000 requests/day) can handle a small production chatbot. Google Gemini 2.0 Flash unlimited tier is genuinely production-viable. Combine multiple free tiers and you can run a full-featured application.</p>

            <p><strong>Q: Which free tier gives the most value for code generation?</strong></p>
            <p>A: Groq free tier with Llama models, OpenRouter 50 free requests/day, and Google Gemini 2.0 Flash are your best options for coding on a zero budget.</p>

            <h2>Final Comparison: Free Tier Verdict</h2>
            <table class="w-full text-sm">
              <thead><tr class="bg-gray-100"><th class="px-3 py-2 text-left">Category</th><th class="px-3 py-2 text-left">Winner</th><th class="px-3 py-2 text-left">Why</th></tr></thead>
